<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>Good idea except.....</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?Gray Rage (DB)">Gray Rage (DB)</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 5:13 a.m. 20/2/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> Good idea except.....<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/pvp.cgi?read=1072" TARGET=_self>One other thought...</A> (Ndaven)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>> Yeah, I know, it's a touchy subject, BUT... Wouldn't it make

<BR>&gt; sense to have looting effect faction standing as well? So if you
<BR>&gt; go around looting bodies you haven't killed, you will still take
<BR>&gt; hits? It *could* even have an RP basis - if you took seperate
<BR>&gt; hits for killing and looting, you could play a nobler character
<BR>&gt; who will kill but not steal from the dead.. actions like that
<BR>&gt; would be more respected, so you wouldn't become AS hated.. :)
<P>&gt; Of course, I could just be showing my newbie status again, so
<BR>&gt; I'll shut up now.
<P>It's a good idea indeed accept I would think the evil charcter would gain in Faction standing for looting as it is an evil act *grins* which would still annoy the victim to no end. Maybe make it so looting is the same as killin' IE if one is a Dark Elf and loots a Dark Elf then he is Faction hit just like killin' a dark elf. BUT, if that same dark elf loots a human his faction might go UP with the dark elven society!
<P>I still think that knowing the name of your looter would be a BIG solution to this problem. IE when someone loots you his name is spiritually given to you after you res. No more slinking and looting....with that system in place looters will be known as looters!
<P>-Gray
<BR>
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
